    "History": {
      "rows": [
        [
          "Staff Generated Concept",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Created By:"
        ],
        [
          "Refugee of Las Vegas, you are an Assamite Warrior who chose to come in out of the cold rather than join the Web of Knives in the mountain.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Jennifer Wolfe"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Your last name is a bit of a misnomer, as you were never a lord/lady. You were little more than a street urchin in Constantinople, before it was Istanbul, making your way by listening and sell information to those with coin for it. You received the moniker mostly as a joke, the \"lord/lady of the streets\" and you made it work for you. You at least survived till early-adulthood, which is more than most. Things changed, however, with the Great War and the rise of modern Turkey from the ashes. You used it as an opportunity to better yourself, fitting into this new culture with a new name, pretending as if you weren't ever more than a homeless gutter rat. But others were wise to you, but they saw potential in your ability to hide in plain sight. Your sire brought you to the Mountain and Embraced you, hoping to make a spy out of you. You were sent to Europe, mingling in the hedonistic and decadent courts of the Camarilla there, learning their ways while blending in, before being sent to the more up-and-coming courts of America. You settled in Vegas primarily because it was so new, everyone was so transient, and few would noticed you. It seemed as convenient a place as any to use as a base of operations as you traveled. You lived outside of the domain, so as not to cross Benedic, and roamed as you were ordered. Then, you received word from your sire what had happened. The last message he sent you was that the Mountain was no longer home and to find protection in the very sect you had been spying on for decades. Since you already had a base in Vegas, and hoping the laxadasical Benedic would overlook large parts of what you had been up to for the last few decades, you've settled here, especially because of the protections you've built here and the Web of Knives hunting you.\n\nYou stayed in Vegas, even after the death of Benedic and the rise of Anthony Sands as Prince. You thought you would be safe there, particularly after the hearts blood was cut off from Alamut's prying eyes and the Web of Knives found it harder to track you. You didn't expect your hunters to be all too human. You have always had an ear to the ground and heard what was coming long before the others in the domain. You gave as many as you could , Camarilla and Independent, warning that the hunters were coming. Those that could fled. For your warning to him, Dante Giovanni gave you a key and information on a haven in Los Angeles where you could escape. It's not much, but it's better than being found by these new human hunters. You don't know what's going on yet, hell, you don't know if Dante got out or anyone else from Vegas. But you are here in LA, and you could hopefully be safe. But that's what you thought about Vegas."
        ],
